Legal Calculus 4.5 — Tier 6: Procedural Sovereignty — Module 64
📘 Legal Calculus — Module 64

Relief Pending Appeal — Stay or Injunction

⚖️ Core Message

If you lose now but can win later, seek a stay or injunction pending appeal.
📖 Lesson Content

1. Standards: likelihood of success; irreparable harm; equities; public interest.
2. Sequence: request in trial court first, then appellate court if denied.
3. Security: address bond (Rule 62/FRAP 8) with evidence and narrow tailoring.
4. Package: proposed order with short findings; timeline of harm.
📝 Assignment

Draft a 'Motion for Injunction Pending Appeal' with a one-paragraph bond proposal and factor headings.
✅ Model Response

MOTION FOR INJUNCTION PENDING APPEAL (excerpt)

I. Likelihood of Success — [short cite]

II. Irreparable Harm — [record cite]

III. Balance of Equities — [point]

IV. Public Interest — [point]

Bond: propose [$] supported by sworn cost declaration (Ex. A).

 

💡 Reflection Summary

Losing today can still protect tomorrow.
🎨 Visual Concept

A pause icon overlaying a courthouse with a small 'appeal' arrow.
